magnetism /ˈmæɡnɪˌtɪzəm/

1. N-UNCOUNT Someone or something that has magnetism has unusual, powerful, and exciting qualities which attract people to them. 魅力 

例： There was no doubting the animal magnetism of the man. 那个男人的动物性魅力无可置疑。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Magnetism is the natural power of some objects and substances, especially iron, to attract other objects toward them. 磁性 

例： ...his research in electricity and magnetism. …他在电、磁领域的研究。

